About the Department
The Human Resources function balances organisational aspirations and employee needs, as we accelerate and strengthen people capabilities to enable sustainable business growth at UOB. Our team of Human Resources specialists are guided by four employee commitments: do what is right, build meaningful careers, make a real difference and lead by positive example.

Overview of the Role
The role is responsible for strengthening Human Resources’ risk management, compliance, and internal control environment. The role ensures that all HR policies, guidelines, and processes comply with regulatory requirements, internal policies, and operational risk standards. This position collaborates closely with internal HR and relevant SMEs (e.g., Operational Risk Management (ORM), Compliance, Legal, Audit, and regulatory authorities) to maintain safe, effective, and compliant HR Operations.

Job Responsibilities
• Provide advisory from Risk & Control (R&C) perspective on all HR policies, guidelines and processes and work with relevant stakeholders to ensure HR practices adhere to risk, compliance, and governance standards;
• Improve HR processes in governance, operational risk, and regulatory compliance areas to strengthen control effectiveness, and ensure compliance;
• Manage HR’s Operational Risk and Compliance activities, to ensure full adherence to internal policies, regulatory requirements, and labor-related laws, including:
o Key Risk & Control Self-Assessment (KRCSA) and Key Operational Risk Indicators (KORI) monitoring;
o Oversight of the Risk Culture Dashboard and facilitation of Risk Culture Self-Assessments;
o Monitoring operational risk incidents, including timely escalation, documentation, and follow up remediation;
o Anti-Money Laundering Control Self-Assessment (AML CSA);
o Regulatory Risk Assessment and support for relevant Compliance review exercises;
o Managing outsourcing and non-outsourcing vendor activities related to HR services, ensuring vendor selection, contracting, and due diligence processes comply with the Bank’s vendor management policies;
o Strengthening HR data protection controls and promoting awareness across HR to maintain full compliance with applicable laws governing employee and candidate information.
• Liaise with relevant authorities when required, including SBV Trade Union, DOHA, Social Insurance Authority, Tax Authority, and others as applicable;
• Serve as HR’s Business Continuity Management Champion, maintaining HR BCP documentation and coordinating with bank-wide exercises to uphold readiness for business continuity requirements;
• Conduct periodic R&C testing and training within HR to strengthen risk awareness, reinforce compliance ownership, and enhance control maturity;
• Represent HR in engagements with internal and external auditors on HR-related audit exercises, ensuring accurate information provision, and effective coordination, monitor and track all action plans arising from audits, compliance reviews, and risk assessments to ensure timely implementation and closure.
• Contribute partly or fully to HR and/or Bank-wide projects/ initiatives/ exercises.

